author: Vox
description:
Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman visits a newly gold-adorned Oval Office, walking away with chips, fighter jets, and upgraded security ties. A major corruption scandal erupts inside Zelensky’s government just as Washington pushes a new peace plan for Ukraine. And a tabletop exercise mapping the risks of shifting thousands of national-security personnel away from counterterrorism, cyber, and sanctions work and into immigration enforcement, and what those trade-offs mean for America’s ability to respond to real threats. “When Washington Smells Weakness,” Episode 3 of The Long Game.

New episodes drop on Fridays, subscribe to The Long Game on it's official YouTube channel for all future episodes: https://www.youtube.com/@podlonggame?sub_confirmation=1 

Chapters: 
0:00 - Today’s Agenda: Russia’s Demands, Corruption in Ukraine, and U.S. National Security Shifts
3:04 - Oval Office Spectacle: Trump & MBS
11:30 - What MBS Got (and didn’t) From Washington
14:33 - Attention on Sudan
23:1
title: Three Crises, One Trump Agenda | The Long Game

author: Vox
description:
Having mixed feelings about your relationship is very common, and it can come and go in phases. You may move through periods where you feel confident your partner sees you, hears you, understands you, and other times where the connection is strained. Vox correspondent Allie Volpe breaks down how to get out of a period of ambivalence — or when to know it’s time to leave. #Relationships #Ambivalence #Partnership

author: Vox
description:
If you’re relying on a simple pro/con list to make some of the biggest decisions of your life, you’re selling yourself short. As the philosopher Ruth Chang points out, life-altering choices are rarely straightforward, and often neither option is superior. Instead of trying to quantify the unquantifiable, consider who you want to become — and how each path might shape your character, your values, and your future. #philosophy #proscons
